HEADWORD: Crith
<hw>Crith</hw> <pr>(kr⟦icr⟧th)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>kriqh`</grk> a barleycorn, a small weight.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The unit for estimating the weight of
a⟦eum⟧riform substances; -- the weight of a liter of hydrogen at 0⟦deg⟧
centigrade, and with a tension of 76 centimeters of mercury. It is
0.0896 of a gram, or 1.38274 grains.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

